Looks like you got the optimal order:
```julia&gt; function d6!(diff, X)
       d,n = size(X)
       @inbounds for i=1:n, j=1:n, dim=1:d
               diff[i,j,dim] = X[dim,i] - X[dim,j]
       end
       diff
       end;

julia&gt; @btime d6!($diff, $X);
  475.010 ns (0 allocations: 0 bytes)

julia&gt; function d7!(diff, X)
       d,n = size(X)
       @inbounds for dim=1:d, i=1:n, j=1:n
               diff[i,j,dim] = X[dim,i] - X[dim,j]
       end
       diff
       end;

julia&gt; @btime d7!($diff, $X);
  746.826 ns (0 allocations: 0 bytes)```

